All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Camp
Represents a camp.
CampAttendee
Represents a camp attendee of a certain camp.
CampCommittee
Represents a camp committee member of a certain camp.
CampFullException
Represents the exception for when the camp is full by generating a message for the user.
CampInformation
Represents the information regarding a camp.
CampManager
CampsManager serve as a proxy between students and camps; students only know the camp name and need to go through here to actually access the camp objects.
CampNotFoundException
Represents exception for when camp is not found
CampRole
Represents a camp role for a student, which can be either attendee or committee (ie both CampAttendee and CampCommittee inherit from this class).
CAMSApp
The entry point to the Camp Application and Management System (CAMS).
CommitteeInterface
Represents a interface that contains abstract methods to be implemented in CampCommittee class
CommitteeWithdrawException
Represents exception for when camp committee tries to withdraw from camp
DateAfterDateException
Represents an exception to ensure that the end date set exceeds the start date
DateClashException
Represents an exception for when there is a clash in date between any 2 camps.
DeadlineOverException
Represents the exception for when a camp registration deadline has passed
Enquiry
Represents an enquiry for a camp.

Represents an exception for when the maximum capacity of a camp has been exceeded.
